sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Modify User Shell Folders Startup Value
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detect modification of the startup key to a path where a payload could be stored to be launched during startup
Detects a Windows program executable started from a suspicious folder

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: CSRSS.exe spawned from unusual location (possible mimicking) (via cmdline)
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: This rule looks for csrss spawning from outside of the normal system32 path. No csrss does not exist within Syswow64.
Detects process creation events that use the Sysnative folder (common for CobaltStrike spawns)

match_context.values: @{EventID=0; CommandLine=C:\Windows\Sysnative\cmd.exe /C "netsh advfirewall firewall add rule name="csrss" dir=in action=allow program="C:\Windows\rss\csrss.exe" enable=yes"; Image=C:\Windows\Sysnative\cmd.exe}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Use Short Name Path in Command Line
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detect use of the Windows 8.3 short name. Which could be used as a method to avoid command-line detection
Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)
